description:
Traditional hotel with good restaurants, close to Hyde Park

For museum lovers
Millennium Gloucester Hotel London Kensington places you within a 10-minute walk of several top-notch cultural attractions, including the Natural History Museum and the Victoria and Albert Museum. You'll be less than a block from Gloucester Road Tube Station.

Parks and palaces
This hotel is just a 15-minute walk from Hyde Park, home of Kensington Palace and Gardens. You'll also be just a 20-minute stroll from attractions like the Royal Albert Hall and Harrods department store.

Eclectic dining
Millennium Gloucester offers several restaurant options, including breakfast at South West 7, Chinese dishes at Bugis Street Brasserie, and Indian curries at Bombay Brasserie. You'll also find a conference center with 25 meeting rooms for a wide range of events.

Classic comfort
Nicely decorated guestrooms are all equipped with WiFi. You'll also enjoy amenities like minibars, flat-screen TVs with satellite channels and pay movies, and facilities for making tea and coffee. Room service runs around the clock.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value:
Perfectly located for exploring London’s top attractions, including Hyde Park, the Royal Albert Hall, the Natural History and Victoria & Albert museums, the Millennium Gloucester Hotel London Kensington provides guests with a convenient central London address.

Millennium Gloucester Hotel London Kensington's lobby is spacious and is dotted with contemporary settees and decorative sculptures. The Millennium Conference Centre offers 25 versatile function rooms with the latest technology for events. A business center, WiFi, and parking are available. Dining options are plentiful and 24-hour room service is available.

DINING.value:
Southwest 7 - Open for breakfast and dinner and provides a nightly buffet of international dishes. Decor has traditional patterned carpeting with sections of wood-panelled flooring with antique-style tables and chairs.

Bugis Street - Modern bistro serving dishes from Singapore and other cuisines of the Far East. Open daily for lunch and dinner. Contemporary decor with French brasserie-style wooden chairs and tables, alongside Far East-style wall prints, lamps and sculptures.

Bombay Brasserie - Indian restaurant

Humphreys - Lobby bar, serving cream teas and sandwiches until late. Leather armchairs and potted plants characterize this traditional lounge-style area.
